      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 19:1-3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Matthew 27:27",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 27:27",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Into the common hall - The original word here means, rather, the governor's palace or dwelling.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The trial of Jesus had taken place outside of the palace. The Jews would not enter in John 18:28, and it is probable that courts were held often in a larger and more public place than would be a room in his dwelling. Jesus, being condemned, was led by the soldiers away from the Jews \"within\" the palace, and subjected there to their profane mockery and sport.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The trial of Jesus had taken place outside of the palace. The Jews would not enter in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 18:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and it is probable that courts were held often in a larger and more public place than would be a room in his dwelling. Jesus, being condemned, was led by the soldiers away from the Jews \"within\" the palace, and subjected there to their profane mockery and sport.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The whole band - The \"band\" or cohort was a tenth part of a Roman legion, and consisted of from 400 to 600 men, according to the size of the legion. Compare the notes at Matthew 8:29.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The whole band - The \"band\" or cohort was a tenth part of a Roman legion, and consisted of from 400 to 600 men, according to the size of the legion. Compare the notes at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
